a) What is the purpose of a modem in a network? Can we connect directly to the internet without it?

Answer: A modem (Modulator-Demodulator) converts digital signals into analog signals and vice versa.

It connects a computer/network to the Internet via ISP.

Without a modem, direct internet connection is not possible in traditional systems.

In fiber networks, ONT is used instead.



